<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF76FE27FE1EFE5A" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" box="[151,510,417,444]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Size. Reaches 
<quantity id="2E379B383F77FFE0FEDBFE27FE91FE5D" box="[314,369,417,444]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F77FFE0FF26FE43FDF0FC39" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF26FE43FBEDFDAD" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Morphology. D VI + I,11; A I,10; P 15–17 (rarely 17). Body moderately elongate, its depth 
<quantity id="2E379B383F77FFE0FB27FE43FAD7FE3E" box="[1222,1335,453,480]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2065" metricValueMax="1.3462" metricValueMin="1.0668" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="4.75" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.2">4.2–5.3 in</quantity>
standard length. Head depressed, snout short, rounded. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin having spines subequal in length, none elongate. Caudal fin rounded, longer than head. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FDA7FDB7FC87FDAA" bold="true" box="[582,871,561,587]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Head and body scaleless</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F77FFE0FC94FDB7FBE0FDAD" author="Hoese, D. F." box="[885,1024,561,588]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref56373" refString="Hoese, D. F. (1986) Descriptions of two new species of Hetereleotris (Pisces: Gobiidae) from the western Indian Ocean, with discussion of related species. The J. L. B Smith Institute of Ichthyology Special Publication, 41, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1986">Hoese 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF26FDD3FEC7FCE1" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FE63FDD3FF1AFD72" bold="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Semitranslucent gray, with 6 irregular, sometimes indistinct, dark yellowish brown bars on body</emphasis>
, containing irregular pale spots, and 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FD4EFDFFFB71FD72" bold="true" box="[687,1169,633,659]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">extending into basal part of dorsal fins</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F77FFE0FB42FDFFFB1BFD72" box="[1187,1275,633,659]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,1113,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-45@40.[175,1412,1113,1939]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 47. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Hetereleotris vulgaris. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Mangrove Bay, El Quseir, Egypt, Red Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601715/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); head with 2 irregular dark brown bands radiating anteroventrally and posteroventrally from eye with a whitish area between them; 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FF3FFD47FCE5FD3A" bold="true" box="[222,773,705,731]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">a narrow dark brown bar at base of caudal fin</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F77FFE0FCF5FD47FC87FD3A" box="[788,871,705,731]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,1113,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-45@40.[175,1412,1113,1939]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 47. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Hetereleotris vulgaris. Photo by S.V. Bogorodsky, Mangrove Bay, El Quseir, Egypt, Red Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601715/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), this fin crossed by irregular vertical rows of dark brown spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF26FC8FFBEFFCC5" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" box="[199,1039,777,804]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F77FFE0FE9EFC8FFD29FCC2" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[383,713,777,803]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Millerigobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FE9EFC8FFD29FCC2" box="[383,713,777,803]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Millerigobius macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F77FFE0FD36FC8FFC95FCC2" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[727,885,777,803]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Zebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zebrus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FD36FC8FFC95FCC2" box="[727,885,777,803]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Zebrus zebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F77FFE0FC62FC8CFBE7FCC2" authorityName="Kovacic, Sanda &amp; Vukic" authorityYear="2021" box="[899,1031,777,804]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Zebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallaoroi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FC62FC8CFC73FCC2" box="[899,915,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Z</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F77FFE0FC41FC8FFBE7FCC2" box="[928,1031,777,803]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">pallaoroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF26FCABFD04FC8D" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<materialsCitation id="59A73C803F77FFE0FF26FCABFD04FC8D" elevation="13" location="Red Sea" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Semenawi Keyih Bahri">
Habitat. No data on habitat for the Mediterranean. In the 
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F77FFE0FCAFFCABFC4EFCA6" box="[846,942,813,839]" country="Eritrea" name="Semenawi Keyih Bahri" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Red Sea</collectingRegion>
, inhabits crevices among stones on reef flat or rocky substrata at coral reefs at depths of 
<quantity id="2E379B383F77FFE0FD69FCD7FD00FC8D" box="[648,736,849,876]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="12.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="1.0">
<elevation id="62E2D1EE3F77FFE0FD69FCD7FD00FC8D" box="[648,736,849,876]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="12.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="1.0">1–24 m</elevation>
</quantity>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F77FFE0FF26FCF3FDF0FC39" blockId="66.[151,1437,417,984]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Geographic distribution. Reported from the Red Sea, Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="2B0BF83F3F77FFE0FC59FCF3FC15FC6E" box="[952,1013,885,911]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Aden</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F77FFE0FBD8FCF3FB6FFC6E" box="[1081,1167,885,911]" name="Yemen" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Socotra</collectingCountry>
Archipelago, south to 
